# Stack Constraints

## Mandatory Stack

| Layer        | Required Technologies                                        |
|-------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Frontend    | Next.js (App Router), shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, React Hook Form |
| Backend     | NestJS, TypeScript strict                                    |
| Database    | PostgreSQL 16 via Prisma                                     |
| Observability | Sentry, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki                          |
| Infra       | Docker Compose                                               |

## Forbidden

- Do NOT use Redux, Zustand, Jotai, or MobX. Use TanStack Query for server state.
- Do NOT use SWR. Only TanStack Query for data fetching.
- Do NOT use Formik or other form libraries. Only React Hook Form.
- Do NOT use MUI, Ant Design, Chakra UI. Only shadcn/ui + Tailwind.
- Do NOT use TypeORM, Sequelize, or Drizzle. Only Prisma.
- Do NOT use Express directly. Use NestJS platform-express.
- Do NOT use raw SQL unless absolutely required (use Prisma query builder).

## When adding new dependencies

1. Check if the functionality already exists in the mandatory stack.
2. If a new library is needed, justify why the mandatory stack cannot cover it.
3. Always prefer smaller, focused packages over large frameworks.
